This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommender systems, which are a common application of collaborative filtering in information retrieval. 

It is also likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a technique for generating large-scale data sets that can be used to train and benchmark recommender systems. 

The paper may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it deals with user/item interaction data sets, which are often modeled as networks in social and information network analysis. 

The Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes a stochastic expansion algorithm for generating large-scale data sets. 

Finally, the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category may be relevant as the paper deals with the scalability of recommender systems, which are often deployed in large-scale production systems.
